Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Grated \Grat"ed\, a. [From 2d {Grate}.] Furnished with a grate or grating; as, grated windows. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Grate \Grate\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Grated}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Grating}.] To furnish with grates; to protect with a grating or crossbars; as, to grate a window. [1913 Webster]
